      <div id="dnn_ContentPane" class="ContentPane"><div class="DnnModule DnnModule-DNN_HTML DnnModule-828 DnnVersionableControl"><a name="828"></a>

<div class="Container-H1"> 
  <!--Container Title-->
  <div class="dnntitle">
  <h1><span id="dnn_ctr828_dnnTITLE_titleLabel" class="title-H1">Communicable Diseases and Chronic Conditions</span>


</h1>
  </div>
  <!--Container Title End--> 
  <!--Container Content-->
  <div class="contentmain">
  
    <div id="dnn_ctr828_ContentPane" class="contentpane"><!-- Start_Module_828 --><div id="dnn_ctr828_ModuleContent" class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC">
	<div id="dnn_ctr828_HtmlModule_lblContent"><p><strong>This section offers data and statistical reports on acute health conditions caused by pathogens and chronic conditions, reported by primary care providers and health care institutions.</strong></p>
<p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/AsthmaData" title="data, state asthma plan and surveillance for asthma">Asthma Data</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/CancerData" title="The Washington State Cancer Registry gathers data to track cancer rates locally, nationally, and worldwide.">Cancer Data</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/CommunicableDiseaseSurveillanceData/CRESurveillance">Carbapenem Resistant Enterobacteriaceae (CRE) Surveillance</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/ChronicDiseaseProfiles" title="Chronic disease profile statistics for Washington State by county">Chronic Disease Profiles</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/ChronicHepatitisSurveillance" title="Chronic hepatitis B and C reporting and surveillance information.">Chronic Hepatitis Surveillance</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/CommunicableDiseaseSurveillanceData" title="Communicable Disease Surveillance Data">Communicable Disease Surveillance Data</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/HealthBehaviors/HealthofWashingtonStateReport">Health of Washington State Report</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/HeartDiseaseStrokeDiabetesDataandPublications" title="Data information for the Heart Disease and Stroke Prevention Program.">Heart Disease, Stroke, and Diabetes</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/HIVAIDSData" title="HIV Statistics and Research Homepage with access to epidemiology and surveillance reports, fact sheets and more...">HIV/AIDS Data</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/NewbornScreeningStatistics" title="Chart showing newborn screening statistics for disorders commonly screened for in Washington State.">Newborn Screening Statistics</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/Obesity" title="Information risk factors and data on rates for obesity in Washington State.">Obesity</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/OralHealth">Oral Health</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/SexuallyTransmittedDisease" title="Reports including morbidity data, incidence rates by county, and the following STDs: Chlamydia, Gonorrhea, Syphilis, Herpes simplex-initial genital infection &amp; Uncommon STDs - including chancroid, lymphogranuloma venereum (LGV) and granuloma inguinale (GI). ">Sexually Transmitted Disease</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/TuberculosisDataandReports" title="Tuberculosis data and reports for Washington State.">Tuberculosis Data and Reports</a></li>
    <li><a href="/DataandStatisticalReports/DiseasesandChronicConditions/WestNileVirus" title="2015 West Nile virus surveillance actitivy in Washington.">West Nile Virus</a></li>
</ul>
</p>
<h3>Surveillance</h3>
<p>The department maintains data and statistical reports on diseases and conditions. Sources of data include reports by health care providers, hospitalization data, death records, studies, and community surveys.&nbsp;</p>
<p>These data summarize trends in notifiable communicable diseases reported by local health jurisdictions to the department. Reported cases often represent only a fraction of the actual burden of disease.</p>
<p>The accuracy of this information has limitations, due to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Sick people who do not seek healthcare</li>
    <li>Healthcare providers and others who do not always recognize, confirm or report notifiable conditions.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h3>Chronic diseases/conditions</h3>
<p>A <strong>chronic</strong> disease persists over a long period of time or recurs. Some chronic diseases, such as chronic hepatitis and HIV are caused by pathogens (germs). Others are causes by behaviors (some types of heart disease, cancer, etc), the environment (some asthma and cancer), or genetics (some birth defects and cancer). Sometimes the cause of chronic conditions is not fully known or there may be a combination of causes.&nbsp;Chronic diseases or conditions include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Asthma</li>
    <li>HIV</li>
    <li>Birth defects (and other special healthcare needs of children)</li>
    <li>Cancer</li>
    <li>Chronic hepatitis </li>
    <li>Diabetes </li>
    <li>Heart Disease and Stroke </li>
    <li>Obesity</li>
</ul>
<h3>
Acute diseases
</h3>
<p>An <strong>acute</strong> disease is a disease with a rapid onset and/or a short course. Many acute diseases are caused by pathogens (germs). Acute diseases include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Sexually Transmitted Diseases </li>
    <li>Tuberculosis</li>
    <li>Other communicable diseases (including: enteric/foodborne disease, vaccine preventable disease, zoonotic disease, acute hepatitis)</li>
</ul></div>
